Economists told us not to zero-sum globalism. So we zero-summed globalim. Economic wealth was coverted to cash, and that cash was wasted. Our vast economic wealth will be plundered. Only then will mangement failure be obvious.

Economics as a management paradigm came to the forefront in 1972. It's been downhill ever since. Econmics insists on the worthlessness of humans. How economics ever came to be called a social science is beyond me. Money before people is not social.

All the box-making robots I've ever worked with failed constantly. You had to cut the tape on trapazoidal boxes, make them rectangular, and retape them. These robots had several mechanics. These robots took breaks all the time.
It's these bottom of the market jobs that people take after their unemployment runs out. Keeping people working, aka spending, is an economic necessity.

The burger joint I worked at had a particular bun. When it was toasted, the burger was done. But, the bun baker went out of business, so the bun clock stopped working. The grill guy had to poke the burgers. Owner asked why. Geez. He didn't understand his sytem.
How does it know if the burger is done?
Sure. What's the upside? Did they hire a mechanic yet, or is the vendor bearing those costs? How do they keep the employees safe?
So where is the corresponding story of the person that use to do that job? Did they file for unemployment today, food stamps? Did they get evicted? Are they sleeping in their car.
Glad to have you!
